# CODEOWNERS makes the privileged CI trust boundary independently review-gated.
#
# GitHub requires a review from a listed owner before these paths can change on a
# branch-protected default branch. Combined with the workflows sourcing the privileged
# Bubblewrap helper from the immutable trusted base checkout, this ensures a pull request
# cannot alter what runs as root in CI (the helper, its pinned digest, the workflow logic,
# or this ownership rule itself) without an owner's review.
#
# Owners must be valid GitHub code owners: a user or a team with write access to the repo,
# never a bare organization handle (an org name is not a valid code owner and GitHub
# silently ignores it). "@mikegtech" is an admin collaborator on this repository.
#
# NOTE: this file only declares intent in-repository. Enforcement additionally requires an
# administrator to enable branch protection on the default branch with "Require a pull
# request before merging" and "Require review from Code Owners". Until that protection is
# configured, CODEOWNERS does not by itself block changes to the privileged CI surface.

# Default ownership for everything not matched below.
*                                        @mikegtech

# Privileged CI surface: workflows and the sudo-bearing sandbox helper.
/.github/workflows/                      @mikegtech
/.github/CODEOWNERS                      @mikegtech
/scripts/ci/                             @mikegtech
/scripts/ci/configure_bwrap_apparmor.sh  @mikegtech

# Immutable capability policy and adapters that gate agent execution.
/.ai/profiles/                           @mikegtech
/.ai/policies/                           @mikegtech
/.ai/providers/                          @mikegtech
/.ai/schemas/                            @mikegtech
/.ai/codex/                              @mikegtech
